---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-mofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/quickbooks/help/",
  "slug": "help",
  "tierClass": "section--tier-guide",
  "bodyClass": "page--mofu",
  "title": "QuickBooks Help · Direct Support from Certified ProAdvisors · TechBrot",
  "description": "QuickBooks help from Certified Intuit ProAdvisors — cleanup, setup, migration, payroll fixes, error resolution, ongoing bookkeeping. Same-day diagnostic for emergencies. Written fixed-fee scope. Independent ProAdvisor firm. Not affiliated with Intuit Inc.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "QuickBooks", "href": "/quickbooks/" },
    { "name": "Help" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "QuickBooks help",
    "heading": "QuickBooks help, delivered by ProAdvisors.",
    "subheading": "The full spectrum of operational QuickBooks help &mdash; setup, cleanup, migration, payroll configuration, error resolution, file repair, multi-state tax setup, ongoing bookkeeping. Same-day diagnostic for emergencies. Written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days. Delivered by Certified Intuit ProAdvisors. Independent firm.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=qb-help", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>Operational QuickBooks help</strong> from Certified ProAdvisors &mdash; the work that lives inside QuickBooks: file setup, structural cleanup, Desktop migration, payroll configuration, multi-state tax setup, error resolution, file repair, and ongoing monthly bookkeeping. Fixed-fee, written scope, same-day diagnostic for emergencies. Across QBO Level&nbsp;2, Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll.",
    "source": "Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not Intuit&rsquo;s software support. Not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Start here",
    "heading": "Get QuickBooks help from a Certified ProAdvisor.",
    "lede": "Send your file for a free review, or book a free 30-minute discovery call. We&rsquo;ll surface the actual issue and recommend the right engagement &mdash; with a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days, before any work begins.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=qb-help", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact" id="help-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure">
      <strong>TechBrot is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not QuickBooks&rsquo; official support.</strong> For Intuit software-level issues (login, billing, subscription, software bugs), Intuit&rsquo;s own support is the right path. We provide independent, operational help with the accounting work <em>inside</em> QuickBooks. QuickBooks and Intuit are registered trademarks of Intuit Inc.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="help-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What we mean</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What &ldquo;QuickBooks help&rdquo; actually means here.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>TechBrot is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm that delivers <strong>operational</strong> QuickBooks help to U.S. small and mid-sized businesses. Operational is the key word: we handle the work that lives inside QuickBooks &mdash; <a href="/quickbooks/setup/?intent=quickbooks-setup">file setup</a>, <a href="/quickbooks/cleanup/?intent=qb-cleanup">structural cleanup</a>, <a href="/quickbooks/migration/?intent=quickbooks-migration">Desktop migration</a>, <a href="/accounting/payroll-management/?intent=payroll">payroll configuration</a>, multi-state tax setup, error resolution, file repair, and ongoing <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">monthly bookkeeping</a>.</p>
      <p>We do not provide Intuit&rsquo;s own software-level support (login issues, billing, software bugs) &mdash; for those, Intuit&rsquo;s official support is the right path. Every engagement is fixed-fee with a written scope. Same-day diagnostic for emergencies (file corruption, payroll-day failures, year-end deadlines); written scope within 3 business days for scoping conversations. Certified ProAdvisors across all four core platforms &mdash; QBO Level&nbsp;2, Desktop, Enterprise, Payroll &mdash; verifiable on Intuit&rsquo;s public ProAdvisor directory.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="help-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks help, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="help-triage">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The diagnostic triage model</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What kind of QuickBooks help do you actually need?</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Find your situation &mdash; each routes to the right engagement, with an honest scope and a typical fee.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for t in triage %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ t.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ t.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ t.href }}">{{ t.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="help-urgency">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">By urgency</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How fast can we help?</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for u in urgency %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ u.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ u.who | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose"><strong>Best path:</strong> {% if u.tel %}<a href="tel:{{ site.phone.e164 }}" data-tb-event="phone_click">{{ u.path | safe }}</a>{% else %}{{ u.path | safe }}{% endif %}</p>
        <p class="prose"><em>Honest scope:</em> {{ u.scope | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="help-problems">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common issues</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The QuickBooks problems most U.S. businesses run into.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for p in problems %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="help-operational">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What it actually looks like</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What QuickBooks help delivers operationally.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Most &ldquo;QuickBooks help&rdquo; offerings are either too narrow (a one-hour consulting call) or too vague (an ongoing &ldquo;support package&rdquo; with no defined deliverables). TechBrot&rsquo;s engagements are scoped as specific operational projects with specific written deliverables &mdash; a cleanup delivers a reconciled, CPA-ready file with a written summary of what was fixed; a setup delivers a configured file ready to operate from day one; a migration delivers a successfully migrated file with reconciled historical data and rebuilt integrations.</p>
      <p>The work is delivered <strong>inside your QuickBooks file</strong> &mdash; we access as accountant-users, you keep your data, and the audit trail is visible to you at any time. We never operate in a parallel system or require a data export. For recurring engagements, the deliverable is the same shape every month: reconciliation, categorization, financial statements, named-ProAdvisor ownership, and a CPA-ready year-end handoff.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="help-services">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Routed properly</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">All QuickBooks help, routed properly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in services %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="review-card__role">{{ s.num | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ s.fee | safe }}</strong> &middot; {{ s.eng | safe }}</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="help-operator">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Who delivers the help</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Certified ProAdvisors. Every engagement. Every time.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot QuickBooks engagement is delivered by a Certified Intuit QuickBooks ProAdvisor &mdash; not a general bookkeeper, not an offshore queue, not a junior associate. The ProAdvisor team holds active Intuit certifications across all four core platforms: QuickBooks Online (Level 2), Desktop, Enterprise, and Payroll. Renewed annually, verifiable on Intuit&rsquo;s public ProAdvisor directory. The certification is the operational signal &mdash; technical proficiency on the platform you&rsquo;ll be billed for work inside, and third-party accountability to a credentialing body.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="help-costs">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Pricing</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What QuickBooks help typically costs.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">All engagements: fixed fee, written scope, no hourly billing. The discovery call is free and no-obligation; specific quotes follow the diagnostic within 3 business days.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in costs %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ c.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose"><strong>For:</strong> {{ c.forWhom | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for b in c.bullets %}<li>{{ b | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="help-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions before you call.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="help-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="help-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="help-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., an independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for accuracy on the boundary between operational ProAdvisor help and Intuit&rsquo;s own software support. Where our scope or fees change, this page is updated.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source">Page last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="help-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Where else to go</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where else to go.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
